text: Swainsona extrajacens is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae and is endemic to central Australia. It is an erect, apparently annual plant with imparipinnate leaves with 9 to 25 linear, egg-shaped leaflets, and racemes of purple flowers in racemes of 5 to 10. == References == Category:Faboideae Category:Plants of Australia Category:Plants described in 1990 Category:Taxa named by Joy Thompson
title: Swainsona extrajacens
